oday, Wednesday 3 June, the National Security Council has extended with the prime ministers approved the transition to phase 3 of the phase-out plan from 8 June. Catering sector
The sector may partially reopen. Arcades (eg casinos), banquet and reception rooms will not reopen until 1 July. With regard to the banquet and reception areas, this will be possible with a maximum of 50 people, under the same conditions as the catering industry. Nightclubs are not allowed to open until the end of August, because no safety distance can be foreseen.
In addition to these exceptions, all other catering establishments such as cafes, bars and restaurants will reopen, following a very precise protocol.
The main points of this protocol include:

A distance of 1m50 between the tables;
Maximum 10 people per table;
Each customer must remain seated at their own table;
Waiters must wear masks;
All catering establishments are allowed to stay open until one in the morning, just like the night shops

