"On November 27th, the federal government took new measures to fight against the coronavirus applicable from Tuesday, December 1st, 2020. Reopening of non-essential shops but under strict conditions :
1.respect of the basic rules (disinfect your hands at the entrance, keep your distance, wear a mask);
2. preventive measures must be announced in a visible way;
3.staff receive appropriate training;
4.shopping is to be done alone. The company of children up to and 5.including the age of 18 years is limited as much as possible;
6. a shop visit should last a maximum of 30 minutes;
7. the shop is responsible for managing the queue outside the shop and 8. supervision of customers waiting outside the shop must be organized;
9. one visitor is allowed per 10 m2;
10. large shops of more than 400 m² must provide access control;
11. access to shopping centres, shopping streets and car parks is to be organised by the relevant municipal authorities until January 15th, 2021."

In Belgium, on the 7th of May it was announced:

Next restrictions are applied to restaurants and cafes:

1) The tables are laid out in such a way as to guarantee a distance of at least 1.5 meters between the tables ;
2) A maximum of 4 people per table is authorized;
3) Only seats at the table are authorized;
4) Each person must remain seated at their own table;
5) No service at the bar is authorized;
6) At least one side of the terrace is entirely open at all times and must ensure sufficient ventilation;
7) The consumption of drinks and meals must take place outside;
8) The customer can only access the interior space occasionally and for a short time to use the sanitary facilities, to access the open terrace or to pay the bill;
9) Customers and staff wear a mask or any other fabric alternative in accordance;
10) The opening hours of the open terrace are limited from 8:00 a.m. to 10:00 p.m.

These measures apply until June 30, 2021 inclusive

Starting from the 4th of May, 2020 in Belgium next mass gatherings are permitted:
funeral ceremonies, but only in the presence of a maximum of 15 people, with the maintenance of a distance of 1.5 meters between each person and without the possibility of exposure of the body;
- civil marriages, but only in the presence of the spouses, their witnesses and the civil registrar;
- religious marriages, but only in the presence of the spouses, their witnesses and the minister of religion.

